When the oil is warm (not burning hot), add the garlic and onions and sauté for about five to six minutes or until the onions have become tender and transparent. After the onions are cooked, add the diced tomatoes along with the tomato sauce. Add small amount of water, so the sauce does not become too thick. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/61/Make-a-Healthy-New-York-Style-Pizza-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Healthy-New-York-Style-Pizza-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/6/61/Make-a-Healthy-New-York-Style-Pizza-Step-6Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Healthy-New-York-Style-Pizza-Step-6Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Next, add the black pepper and the salsa. The salsa gives a spicy kick to the pizza and is used by many New York Pizzerias. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5a/Make-a-Healthy-New-York-Style-Pizza-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-a-Healthy-New-York-Style-Pizza-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/5a/Make-a-Healthy-New-York-Style-Pizza-Step-6Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-a-Healthy-New-York-Style-Pizza-Step-6Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
